-- Terrestar Networks Files for Bankruptcy Owing Creditors Up to $1 Billion
-- B y   D a w n   M c C a r t y   a n d   D a v i d   M c L a u g h l i n
-- 2010-10-19T20:55:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/terrestar-networks-files-for-bankruptcy-owing-creditors-up-to-1-billion.html
TerreStar Networks Inc. , a provider
of mobile and Internet communications services, filed for
bankruptcy in New York, saying it owes creditors more than
$1 billion.  TerreStar reported assets and liabilities of more than
$1 billion each in documents filed today in the U.S. Bankruptcy
Court in Manhattan. The largest unsecured creditors are
noteholders with a claim of $178.6 million, according to court
papers.  TerreStar, based in Reston, Virginia, said in a regulatory
filing in August that it was in discussions with certain
noteholders about a restructuring and that it might have to file
for bankruptcy.  The case is In re: TerreStar Networks Inc., No. 10-15446,
U.S. Bankruptcy Court, Southern District of New York,
(Manhattan).  To contact the reporters on this story:
